# Detail modal (`src/app/shared/detail-modal`)

Global imperative read-only detail modal for table **View Details** row actions. Do not use `ConfirmService` for detail views or duplicate modal markup in feature pages.

## Structure

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `detail-modal.types.ts` | `DetailDefinition`, `DetailFieldDef`, `DetailModalOptions`, `DetailModalResult` |
| `define-detail.ts` | `defineDetail<T>()` |
| `detail-modal.constants.ts` | `buildDetailModalActions(scope)`, shared close/edit label keys |
| `detail-modal.service.ts` | `open<T>(options): Observable<DetailModalResult>` |
| `detail-view/` | Renders `DetailDefinition` + entity data |
| `detail-field-renderer/` | Built-in field widgets (text, date, status, route, vehicle, translate) |
| `detail-modal/` | `DetailModalComponent` — single host mounted in app root |
| `index.ts` | Barrel |

## Global host

`app.html` mounts `<app-confirm-dialog />` once (alongside `<router-outlet />`). `PortalShellComponent` mounts `<app-detail-modal />` for portal table detail views. Feature pages only inject `DetailModalService`; no per-page dialog template.

## Per-entity pattern

1. **Definition** — `detail/<entity>.detail.ts` with `defineDetail<Entity>()({ sections: [...] })`.
2. **Opener** — `detail/open-<entity>-detail-modal.ts` calls `DetailModalService.open()` and handles `edit` navigation.
3. **Table page** — `viewDetails` row action calls the opener with `scope: 'all' | 'my'`.

```typescript
// detail/route.detail.ts
export const RouteDetail = defineDetail<Route>()({
  sections: [
    {
      id: 'schedule',
      titleKey: 'portal.user.features.routes.detail.sections.schedule',
      fields: [
        { key: 'status', type: 'status', labelKey: '…table.columns.status' },
        { key: 'transportStartDate', type: 'date', labelKey: '…form.fields.transportStartDate' },
      ],
    },
  ],
});
```

```typescript
// table page
case 'viewDetails':
  openRouteDetailModal(this.detailModalService, this.router, event.row, 'all');
  break;
```

## API

```typescript
import {
  DetailModalService,
  buildDetailModalActions,
  DETAIL_MODAL_EDIT_ACTION_ID,
} from 'shared/detail-modal';

this.detailModalService
  .open({
    titleKey: 'portal.user.features.routes.detail.title',
    subtitleKey: 'portal.user.features.routes.detail.subtitle',
    subtitleParams: { id: row.id },
    definition: RouteDetail,
    data: row,
    actions: buildDetailModalActions('my'), // Edit + Close; 'all' → Close only
  })
  .pipe(take(1))
  .subscribe((result) => {
    if (result.actionId === DETAIL_MODAL_EDIT_ACTION_ID) {
      void this.router.navigateByUrl(userEditRouteUrl(row.id));
    }
  });
```

- Returns `Observable<DetailModalResult>` with `{ actionId }`.
- Backdrop, Escape, and header X → `{ actionId: 'close' }`.
- Only one modal at a time.

## Field types

| `type` | Renders |
|--------|---------|
| `text` | Plain string (empty → em dash) |
| `date` | Formatted date |
| `number` | Formatted number; optional `suffixKey` |
| `status` | `StatusBadgeComponent` |
| `route` | `RouteDisplayComponent` (`originKey`, `destinationKey`) |
| `vehicle` | `VehicleDisplayComponent` (`nameKey`, `plateKey`) |
| `translate` | Enum label via `options` |

Reuse form/table `labelKey`s where possible. Add `…features.<entity>.detail.*` for modal title, subtitle, and section headings only.

## CTA scope

| Scope | Footer actions |
|-------|----------------|
| `'all'` | Close only |
| `'my'` | Edit (secondary) + Close (primary) |

Use `buildDetailModalActions(scope)` — do not hand-roll button defs unless a flow needs custom actions.

## i18n

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `shared.detailModal.common.close` | Default close button |
| `shared.detailModal.common.edit` | Default edit button |
| `…features.<entity>.detail.title` | Modal title |
| `…features.<entity>.detail.subtitle` | Modal subtitle (supports params) |
| `…features.<entity>.detail.sections.*` | Section headings |

## Styling

Theme tokens in `src/styles.scss`:

- `--bg-detail-modal`
- `--border-detail-modal`
- `--shadow-detail-modal`

Panel width `min(100%, 42rem)`. `z-index: 250`. Body scroll locked while open.

## Examples

- Routes: `portal/user/features/routes/detail/`
- Cargo: `portal/user/features/cargo/detail/`
- Storage: `portal/user/features/storage/detail/`

Do not use `ConfirmService` for view details. Do not add a second global detail modal host.
